The paper deals with the problem of routing on graphs, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of treewidth and pathwidth in the problem suggests that it may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and networked systems (cs.NI). The problem also involves capacities on edges and nodes, which may relate to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the optimization aspect of the problem may also place it in the category of game theory (cs.GT).
